GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 347
Short Title: Supporting Parents Who Serve. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Chitlik and Mohammed (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 20, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PERMIT MEMBERS TO BE PRESENT AND VOTING, AS
3 CONSTITUTIONALLY MANDATED, THROUGH THE USE OF PROXY VOTING IN
4 CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. Article 3A of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes is amended by
7 adding a new section to read:
8 "§ 120-11.3. In-person voting by use of proxies.
9 (a) Findings. – The General Assembly of North Carolina finds that advances in
10 technology have allowed meaningful participation even when persons are not physically
11 co-located. The General Assembly further finds that these advances allow a legislator to be
12 present and voting, as contemplated by the Constitution of North Carolina, even if not physically
13 located in the chamber at the time of the vote.
14 (b) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
15 (1) Reserved for future codification purposes.
16 (2) Reserved for future codification purposes.
17 (3) Designated proxy. – The leader of the party of the qualified member's chamber
18 appointed to cast a vote for, and in the manner directed by, the qualified
19 member.
20 (4) Reserved for future codification purposes.
21 (5) Reserved for future codification purposes.
22 (6) Qualified member. – A member of the General Assembly who filed a voting
23 designation with respect to a triggering event.
24 (7) Triggering event. – The occurrence of childbirth, adoption, stillbirth, or
25 miscarriage to a qualified member.
26 (8) Voting designation. – A written submission by a qualified member to, and on
27 a form made available by, the Principal Clerk of the member's chamber that
28 appoints a designated proxy.
29 (c) Proxy Voting. – The General Assembly shall permit a qualified member not
30 physically located in the chamber to be present and voting by use of a designated proxy. In order
31 to vote by use of a designated proxy, (i) the qualified member shall have filed a voting designation
32 and shall access the real-time, audio or audiovisual stream of each session in which the member
33 votes by use of a designated proxy, (ii) the designated proxy shall be physically located in the
34 chamber when the question is put, and (iii) over one-half of the members of the chamber shall
35 have already voted in the chamber on the question. After the members in the chamber have voted,
*S347-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 the presiding officer shall call on the designated proxy of each qualified member voting pursuant
2 to this subsection.
3 (d) Security; Means. – The General Assembly of North Carolina shall, in accordance with
4 rules adopted by each of the respective bodies, establish a process by which to validate and secure
5 proxy voting conducted pursuant to subsection (c) of this section. Notwithstanding any rules
6 adopted by a chamber to the contrary, the use of electronic devices, as necessary to effectuate the
7 validation required by this subsection, shall be allowed in the chambers.
8 (e) Duration. – A qualified member's voting designation shall be valid until the earlier of
9 (i) 16 weeks from a triggering event or (ii) the date the qualified member revokes the designation
10 in writing on a form made available by, and filed with, the appropriate Principal Clerk."
11 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
